# RMS Conventions

These conventions cannot be inferred from general best practices — they are recorded in `docs/knowledge/sync-protocol.md`, `docs/planning/sprint-1.md`, `docs/planning/backend-stack-discussion.md`. Narrow rules (`huma`, `sqlc-queries`, `goose-dev-migrations`, `hybrid-plan-model`, `react-shadcn-components`, `no-hacks`) extend this file — do not duplicate them.

## IDs

- IDs for `project | plan | room | wall | photo` are generated by the **client** (UUID v7). Server only echoes. No `uuid.New()`, `gen_random_uuid()`, `RETURNING id` for these entities.
- `id` columns are `TEXT PRIMARY KEY`, not `UUID`. This accommodates the client-side UUID v7.
- Exception: `users`, `refresh_tokens`, `workspaces` — server-owned, any ID format.

## Time

- API ↔ client: always `int64` epoch-millis. Fields: `clientUpdatedAt`, `updatedAt`, `deletedAt`, `takenAt`, `expiresAt`. ISO strings in the JSON contract are a bug.
- Inside Postgres: `TIMESTAMPTZ`. Mapping happens at the handler/db boundary.
- LWW and cursor filters **never** use server `time.Now()` — only values from the request body.

## Soft-delete

- Deleting a sync entity: `UPDATE … SET deleted_at = now()`. Never `DELETE FROM`.
- Pull returns rows with `deleted_at IS NOT NULL` as regular changes (tombstones). A `WHERE deleted_at IS NULL` filter in pull queries is a bug.

## `sync_cursor`

- Source: a single Postgres `SEQUENCE` `sync_cursor_seq`, shared across all sync tables.
- Bump only via a `BEFORE INSERT OR UPDATE` trigger. Do not call `nextval` from application code.
- Delta pagination: **only** by `sync_cursor > $since`, not by `updated_at`.

## Workspace

- `workspaceId` — always from JWT claims (`workspaceId`), extracted by middleware into `context.Context`. From body/path/query — bug (sprint 1: one user = one workspace; after shared-workspaces, middleware remains the authorization point).
- Every sync query (`SELECT … FROM <entity>`) must include `workspace_id = $N`. Omission is a data leak.

## Sources of truth

| Domain | Source | What is generated / derived |
|---|---|---|
| DB schema | `apps/api/migrations/001_init.sql` | `apps/api/internal/db/*.go` via sqlc |
| SQL queries | `apps/api/queries/*.sql` | `apps/api/internal/db/*.go` via sqlc |
| API contract | `packages/api-contracts/openapi.yaml` | `packages/api-contracts/types.gen.ts` via openapi-typescript |
| Sync protocol DTOs (Go) | `apps/api/internal/sync/types.go` | manually synced with openapi.yaml |
| Sync decisions | `docs/knowledge/sync-protocol.md` | OpenAPI + Go types must match |
| Hybrid Plan model | `docs/knowledge/hybrid-plan-model.md` | schema + rules |

Changing a source without updating derived artifacts is a bug.

## Codegen obligations

- After editing `apps/api/queries/*.sql` or `apps/api/sqlc.yaml` — `just api-gen`.
- After editing `packages/api-contracts/openapi.yaml` — `just api-gen` (regenerates TS) **and** manual sync of `apps/api/internal/sync/types.go`.
- After editing `apps/api/migrations/001_init.sql` — `just db-reset`.
- Files `apps/api/internal/db/*.go` and `packages/api-contracts/types.gen.ts` are **generated**. Manual edits will be overwritten.

## Commands

- `just check` — canonical verification (`go build` + `go vet` + `pnpm vitest`). Required before PR.
- `just dev` — starts everything (compose + air + pnpm dev).
- `just api-gen` / `just db-reset` / `just migrate` — see above.

## Web ↔ API

- HTTP calls to the API only through `apps/web/src/api/client.ts`: methods call `fetch`, request/response types come from `paths` / `components` in `@rms/api-contracts/types.gen.ts`. Direct `fetch('/api/v1/...')`, `axios`, hand-rolled DTOs in `apps/web/src/` bypassing this layer — bug.
- Requests with caching/retries — via `@tanstack/react-query`, but mutations and endpoint calls still proxy through `api/client.ts` (query hooks only call these functions).
- Web and API share a monorepo specifically for atomic contract refactors; take advantage of this.

## Photos

- Upload — pre-signed PUT in three steps (`POST /photos/upload-url` → `PUT <s3>` → `POST /sync/push` with `PhotoPayload`). Multipart through the API server violates the contract.
- `photoId` is set by the client (UUID v7) in step 1, not the server.

## What NOT to write in this project

- `ALTER TABLE` in a new migration file (see `goose-dev-migrations`).
- Inline SQL via `db.Query("SELECT … " + var)` (see `sqlc-queries`).
- Direct write to `http.ResponseWriter` from a huma handler (see `go-http-handlers`).
- `panic` in the request path (see `go-error-handling`).
- Bypassing React web layer rules (see `react-shadcn-components`).
- Hack fixes without a named invariant (see `no-hacks`).
